pageContext.claim: “You saw last month the trade deficit went way down. Everybody said, "What happened?" Well, what's happening is growth.”
pageContext.analysis: This is highly misleading. The trade deficit has gone up in Trump's two years in office; in fact, it’s up 20.3 percent for the 12 months ending in November, compared with 2016, the year before he took office. There was a small decline from October to November, the most recent data available, but that came after the monthly deficit reached the highest point in 10 full years in October.
